@vinothchandar @prazanna Addressed your comments. 

> We may want to enable adding properties to HoodieRecordPayload with a property in HoodieWriteConfig (disabled by default)

Did not add this property because in the default WriteStatus implementation class (WriteStatusImpl), the metadata map is anyway not used. Also, this adds a dependency to HoodieWriteConfig class from WriteStatus Interface. Open to your suggestions on this.

Some relevant details in https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-17064, but code explanation below, based on [DAGScheduler](https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/scheduler/DAGScheduler.scala#L1351)

**A) There are some fetch failures** 

Spark schedules a resubmit of the stage (ShuffleMapStage mostly[?]) and takes it off `runningStages`

```
// It is likely that we receive multiple FetchFailed for a single stage (because we have
// multiple tasks running concurrently on different executors). In that case, it is
// possible the fetch failure has already been handled by the scheduler.
if (runningStages.contains(failedStage)) {
  logInfo(s"Marking $failedStage (${failedStage.name}) as failed " +
              s"due to a fetch failure from $mapStage (${mapStage.name})")
  markStageAsFinished(failedStage, Some(failureMessage))
}
```

**B) goes on to schedule a resubmit for the stage with a 200ms wait time** 
```
 messageScheduler.schedule(
                new Runnable {
                  override def run(): Unit = eventProcessLoop.post(ResubmitFailedStages)
                },
                DAGScheduler.RESUBMIT_TIMEOUT,
                TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS
              )
```

Resubmit basically grabs all partitions without an output location and submits tasks for it again, which means currently running tasks could be resubmitted

**C) During the 200ms window, more tasks could fail or complete for this stage** 

```
case smt: ShuffleMapTask =>
           val shuffleStage = stage.asInstanceOf[ShuffleMapStage]
           ...
           if (stageIdToStage(task.stageId).latestInfo.attemptId == task.stageAttemptId) {
              // This task was for the currently running attempt of the stage. Since the task
              // completed successfully from the perspective of the TaskSetManager, mark it as
              // no longer pending ...
              shuffleStage.pendingPartitions -= task.partitionId
            }
            ...
            } else {
            ...
              shuffleStage.addOutputLoc(smt.partitionId, status)
              // Remove the task's partition from pending partitions. This may have already been
              // done above, but will not have been done yet in cases where the task attempt was
              // from an earlier attempt of the stage (i.e., not the attempt that's currently
              // running).  This allows the DAGScheduler to mark the stage as complete when one
              // copy of each task has finished successfully, even if the currently active stage
              // still has tasks running.
              shuffleStage.pendingPartitions -= task.partitionId
            }
```

Some of the inconsistency may be coming from this.. 

```
 String COMPACTION_EXTENSION = "." + COMPACTION_ACTION;
  //this is to preserve backwards compatibility on commit in-flight filenames
  String INFLIGHT_COMMIT_EXTENSION = INFLIGHT_EXTENSION;
```

For commit action, we write the inflight as .inflight and then rename to .commit.. but for other we do .deltacommit.inflight and then later rename to .deltacommit..
